'''Josip Šutalo''' (born 28 February 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]. Born in Bosnia and Herzegovina, he plays for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===Dinamo Zagreb===
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen GNK Dinamo Zagreb (UEFA Championsleague 2022-10-05) 47.jpg|thumb|left|Šutalo with [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] in 2022|230x230px]]
In July 2014, Šutalo moved from [[NK Neretva|Neretva]] to the youth academy of [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]. On 1 September 2018, he made his debut for [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb II|Dinamo Zagreb II]] in a 3–1 win against [[NK BSK Bijelo Brdo|Bijelo Brdo]]. On 30 October 2019, he made his debut for Dinamo's first team in a 3–0 victory against [[NK Opatija|Opatija]] in the [[2019–20 Croatian Football Cup|Croatian Cup]]. On 1 July 2020, he made his [[Croatian Football League|Prva HNL]] debut in a 1–0 win against [[NK Inter Zaprešić|Inter Zaprešić]].

On 18 January 2021, Šutalo joined [[NK Istra 1961|Istra 1961]] on loan until the end of the [[2020–21 NK Istra 1961 season|season]]. He made his debut on the next day in the [[2020–21 Croatian First Football League|league]] against [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]], which ended in a 1–1 draw. On 19 May, he played in the [[2021 Croatian Football Cup final|Cup final]], where he scored an own goal as his team lost 6–3 to his parent club Dinamo.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hns-cff.hr/matches/41712762/dinamo-istra-1961/ |title=Dinamo 6–3 Istria 1961 |website=[[Croatian Football Federation]] |language=hr |date=19 May 2021 }}</ref>

He later returned to Dinamo for the [[2021–22 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|2021–22 season]]. On 23 July 2021, he recorded his first goal and assist for Dinamo in a 4–0 win against [[NK Hrvatski Dragovoljac|Hrvatski Dragovoljac]]. He made his debut in the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] on 16 September, as Dinamo lost 2–0 to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033184/ |title=Dinamo Zagreb 0–2 West Ham |website=[[UEFA]] |date=16 September 2021 }}</ref> He scored his first goal in that competition on 4 November in a 3–1 win over [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033233/ |title=Dinamo Zagreb 3–1 Rapid Wien |website=[[UEFA]] |date=4 November 2021 }}</ref> On 6 September 2022, he made his [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 1–0 win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035649/ |title=Dinamo Zagreb 1–0 Chelsea |website=[[UEFA]] |date=6 September 2022 }}</ref>

===Ajax===
On 21 August 2023, Šutalo joined [[Eredivisie]] side [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] for a reported fee of €20.5 million, signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ajax finalise transfer Šutalo |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/ajax-finalise-transfer-sutalo/ |access-date=2023-08-21 |website=[[AFC Ajax]] |language=en-US}}</ref> He made his debut on 3 September and was immediately given the [[Captain (association football)|captain's armband]] for the match, a goalless draw away to [[Fortuna Sittard]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/josip-sutalo-kapetan-ajaxa---800141.html |title=Hrvatu ukazana nevjerojatna čast: "Jučer" došao u slavni klub i odmah postao kapetan! |language=hr |website=[[Gol.hr]] |date=2023-09-03 |accessdate=2023-09-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportnieuws.nl/voetbal/binnenland/wow-josip-sutalo-draagt-de-aanvoerdersband-bij-ajax-debuut/ |title=Wow! Josip Sutalo draagt de aanvoerdersband bij Ajax-debuut |language=nl |date=2023-09-03 |accessdate=2023-09-03 |website=[[Sportnieuws]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/game/fortuna-sittard-vs-ajax-2023-9-3-13-30 |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |title=FortunaSittard and Ajax Draw |date=2023-09-03 |accessdate=2023-09-03 |language=en-US}}</ref>

Šutalo featured regularly in his first season, making 23 appearances and scoring one goal in the Eredivisie, along with 8 appearances in UEFA club competitions as Ajax competed in both the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] and [[UEFA Europa Conference League|Europa Conference League]] during a challenging season for the club.<ref name="SW"/>

In the [[2024–25 AFC Ajax season|2024–25 season]], Šutalo continued as a key player in [[Centre-back|central defence]]. By late March 2025, he had played 21 league matches, scoring two goals,<ref>{{cite web |title=Josip Šutalo - Eredivisie |url=https://eredivisie.eu/clubs/ajax/players/josip-sutalo/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=eredivisie.eu}}</ref> and made 16 appearances in the UEFA Europa League (including qualifiers), scoring once in the qualification rounds.<ref name="SW"/> Known for his ball-playing ability, Šutalo maintained a high pass completion rate (around 93%) and contributed significantly to build-up play.<ref>{{cite web |title=Josip Sutalo Football Statistics - WhoScored.com |url=https://www.whoscored.com/players/402666/show/josip-sutalo |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=WhoScored.com}}</ref><ref name="scoutingstats">{{cite web |title=Josip Šutalo - Stats & Scout Report |url=https://scoutingstats.ai/player/josip-sutalo-4148/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=ScoutingStats.AI}}</ref> He also recorded strong interception numbers during this period.<ref name="scoutingstats"/>

==International career==
Šutalo made his debut for [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]] on 10 June 2022 in a 1–0 victory over [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A#Group 1|Nations League]], having been named in the starting lineup.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 June 2022 |title=VIDEO Josip Šutalo: Ovo sanjaš cijeli život, da sam zamišljao bolje ne bi bilo ovako |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/josip-sutalo-nakon-debija-za-hrvatsku-ovo-sanjas-cijeli-zivot---728329.html |access-date=11 June 2022 |website=[[Dnevnik Nove TV|Gol.hr]] |language=hr}}</ref> On 17 December 2022, he made his debut for Croatia at a major tournament in the 2–1 [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Third place play-off|third place play-off]] victory over [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/sutalo-kome-posvecujem-medalju-sebi-ali-i-obitelji-i-cijeloj-hrvatskoj/2421952.aspx |title=Šutalo: Za ovo sam radio cijeli život |website=[[Index.hr]] |date=2022-12-17 |access-date=2022-12-18 |language=hr |author=HINA |author-link=Croatian News Agency}}</ref> On 5 June 2023, he was named in the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Croatia|final squad]] for the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-objavio-konacan-popis-za-ligu-nacija---785426.html |title=Zlatko Dalić objavio konačan popis za Ligu nacija: Otpao je mladi napadač |website=[[Gol.hr]] |language=hr |author=HINA |author-link=Croatian News Agency |date=5 June 2023 |access-date=3 September 2023}}</ref> playing both games as Croatia finished as [[2023 UEFA Nations League final|runners-up]] to [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/654360 |date=14 June 2023 |accessdate=3 September 2023 |website=[[ESPN]] |language=en-US |title=Netherlands 2-4 Croatia (Jun 14, 2023) Final Score}}</ref><ref name="unlf" />

